{"id":84654,"title":"Ultrasound evaluation of lumbar spine anatomy in newborn infants: implications for optimal performance of lumbar puncture.","abstract":"An ultrasound evaluation of lumbar spine anatomic landmarks relevant for lumbar puncture was performed in 199 newborn infants. Effects of 6 patient positions and gestational age on interspinous process distance, subarachnoid space width, predicted needle entry angle, and needle insertion depth were assessed. Our results identify optimized conditions for lumbar puncture: sitting the infant with hips flexed, a needle entry angle of 65-70 degrees, and proper needle insertion depth (calculated as 2.5 × weight in kilograms + 6 in millimeters). ","date":"2014-09-26","categories":"Pathological Conditions and Signs and Symptoms","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25063721","annotations":[{"name":"Lumbar puncture","weight":0.906012,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lumbar_puncture"},{"name":"Ultrasound","weight":0.796849,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultrasound"},{"name":"Vertebral column","weight":0.793722,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vertebral_column"},{"name":"Anatomy","weight":0.781843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anatomy"},{"name":"Infant","weight":0.636795,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infant"},{"name":"Neonate","weight":0.461051,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neonate"},{"name":"Weight","weight":0.43624,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weight"},{"name":"Subarachnoid space","weight":0.32545,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subarachnoid_space"},{"name":"Gestational age","weight":0.30685,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gestational_age"},{"name":"Flexion","weight":0.285295,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flexion"},{"name":"Lumbar vertebrae","weight":0.252918,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lumba